The article discusses the importance of International Women's Day and the progress that women have made in society. It acknowledges that there is still work to be done to ensure the full participation of women in all areas of life. The United States is committed to empowering women both domestically and internationally by promoting entrepreneurship, education, employment opportunities, and training. The administration has launched initiatives to promote women in business and will continue to work with global partners to ensure equal opportunities for women. The article emphasizes the administration's commitment to fostering economic growth and job creation by harnessing the potential of women in the workforce and addressing barriers they face, such as access to capital, markets, and networking opportunities.